  "text": "HTTP Filter Factory Registration and Per-Connection Instantiation in Envoyproxy/Envoy:\n\n## Factory Registration System\n\nThe filter factory registry is implemented in `envoy/registry/registry.h`, which provides a template-based generic registry pattern:\n- `FactoryRegistry<Base>` maintains a global map of factory instances indexed by name\n- `RegisterFactory<T, Base>` enables static registration of filter factory implementations\n- The `REGISTER_FACTORY` and `LEGACY_REGISTER_FACTORY` macros (defined in registry.h) are used throughout the codebase to register filters\n\n## HTTP Filter Factory Interface\n\nThe `NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory` interface is defined in `envoy/server/filter_config.h`. Each HTTP filter must implement this interface with a factory name. The key method is:\n- `createFilterFactoryFromProto()` - creates an `Http::FilterFactoryCb` from protobuf configuration\n\nThe `Http::FilterFactoryCb` is a callback function type (defined in `envoy/http/filter_factory.h`) that takes `FilterChainFactoryCallbacks&` and creates filter instances for each request.\n\n## Filter Chain Creation Flow\n\n**Configuration Time (startup):**\n1. `HttpConnectionManagerConfig` in `source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.h` implements `Http::FilterChainFactory`\n2. `FilterChainHelper` in `source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h` processes the filter configuration from the protobuf\n3. `FilterChainHelper::processFilter()` looks up the filter factory from the registry and calls `createFilterFactoryFromProto()` to get the `FilterFactoryCb`\n4. These callbacks are stored in `filter_factories_` for later use\n\n**Per-Request Instantiation (runtime):**\n1. When a new HTTP request arrives, `HttpConnectionManagerImpl::newStream()` creates a new `FilterManager`\n2. `FilterManager::createFilterChain()` is called (in `source/common/http/filter_manager.cc`)\n3. This calls `HttpConnectionManagerConfig::createFilterChain()` which calls `FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories()` (in `source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.cc`)\n4. For each stored `FilterFactoryCb`, it calls `FilterManager::applyFilterFactoryCb()`\n5. `applyFilterFactoryCb()` creates a `FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl` and invokes the `FilterFactoryCb` with it\n\n## Per-Request Filter Instantiation\n\nThe `FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl` class (defined in `source/common/http/filter_manager.h`) implements the `FilterChainFactoryCallbacks` interface and handles the actual filter instantiation:\n\n- `addStreamDecoderFilter()` - creates an `ActiveStreamDecoderFilter` wrapper around the filter instance and adds it to the decoder filter chain\n- `addStreamEncoderFilter()` - creates an `ActiveStreamEncoderFilter` wrapper and adds it to the encoder filter chain\n- `addStreamFilter()` - creates both wrapper types for bidirectional filters\n\nThe `ActiveStreamDecoderFilter` and `ActiveStreamEncoderFilter` wrappers (defined in `source/common/http/filter_manager.h`) manage the filter lifecycle, handle iteration state, and invoke the actual filter methods.\n\n## Concrete Example\n\nThe Router filter implementation in `source/extensions/filters/http/router/config.cc` demonstrates the pattern:\n- `RouterFilterConfig` inherits from `FactoryBase<...>` (defined in `source/extensions/filters/http/common/factory_base.h`)\n- `createFilterFactoryFromProtoTyped()` returns a lambda function that is the `FilterFactoryCb`\n- This lambda captures the filter configuration and, when called during filter chain creation, uses `callbacks.addStreamDecoderFilter()` to instantiate a `Router::ProdFilter` for the current request\n- The filter is registered via `LEGACY_REGISTER_FACTORY` macro, adding it to the global factory registry"
}

